==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Paleozoic
<hw>Pa`le*o*zo"ic</hw> <pr>(p⟦amac⟧`l⟦esl⟧*⟦osl⟧*z⟦omac⟧"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Paleo-</ets> + Gr. <grk>zwh`</grk> life, fr.
<grk>zh^n</grk> to live.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining
to, or designating, the older division of geological time during which
life is known to have existed, including the Silurian, Devonian, and
Carboniferous ages, and also to the life or rocks of those ages. See
<xex>Chart</xex> of <er>Geology</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paleozoic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Paleozoic
<hw>Pa`le*o*zo"ic</hw> <pr>(p⟦amac⟧`l⟦esl⟧*⟦osl⟧*z⟦omac⟧"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>The Paleozoic time or
strata.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paleozoology</ent>⟦br⟧
